			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">If you want to play "for fun," yes, it is a blast.</span>
<br />

<br />
If you have even the smallest twinkling of thinking that you want to aggressively raid. Absolutely not. DPS? Go wizard if you want to cast, rogue if you like melee. Pick a utility class otherwise. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Do NOT go mage if you ever even dream of raiding at the higher levels until you see confirmation here that meaningful balance has been achieved. </span>
<br />

<br />
SOE has boxed themselves into a corner and the pets will likely never be able to do anything useful at those levels, except suck your mana just to keep them alive rather than causing damage. 
<br />

<br />
They are working on it right now, but until a truly viable, long-term solution is actually pushed live, I'd hold off, or at least consider bringing up another toon as well.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
