				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I started my mage, I thought that someday I might hit the 50s. My biggest goal was to be able to "catch up" with the RL friend that introduced me to EQ and join him in his guild. I thought VP was the end-all and be-all of the game from reading EQ Atlas. I thought that epics were really the best thing a player could ever get in the game.
<br />

<br />
By the time I was in NToV, I was firmly attached to Itchy. By the time I realized that I would be gunning for the elementals, there was no way to go back, due to NO DROP gear as well as the need to have an established reputation.
<br />

<br />
So I raise a warning flag based on my experience...<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
