			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You seriously only get mad and or irritated at the mage class short comings if you happen to be a full time raider.  In a group Mages still excell, many many people chose use over wizards (in my experience only), you have a measure of soloability 1-60 but it takes skill, you have a lot of trial and error ahead of you. We are excellent cash farmers, Myself at level 65 with semi-decent just above bazaar gear, can solo 2 of the Kunark dragons for cash, and I do. Notice when you start a mage the tag says  High Difficulty? its not a joke. you need skill and patience.
<br />

<br />
Wizards can solo, and they have a huge rate of groupability, they are a must-have in high end raids for damage.  They are limited to out-door areas, which means if you solo with one, you forgo the XP modifiers of a dungeon, Which in turn also means alot of the loot you could get is also going to slip away since many farmed drops/items/gems are found in dungeons.
<br />

<br />
Mages are a VERY good class, they are a blast to play, and its pretty much only when you get to a raiding level that short-comings start appearing. But yanno, a little faith in the pot, our pets may be semi-sorta updated by the time you get to this level of the game.
<br />

<br />
Good luck.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=389452&resize=true" target="_blank">Tanakin Zi'Rikiel </a>
