			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We were waiting on the 6th member for an LDoN adventure a few days ago. 
<br />

<br />
latecomer show up, apologizes for being late, saying they were dropping off some twink gear for a friend of theirs who had just started playing. Here's how the conversation went from there:
<br />

<br />
"oh really, what class does he play?" 
<br />

<br />
"mage"
<br />

<br />
"really?"
<br />

<br />
"hahahahaha"
<br />

<br />
"rofl"
<br />

<br />
"How high is he? Can you get him to change his mind?"
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway, on a more constructive note, mage is pretty fun at lower levels, you can solo pretty well up 50 or so, then to 60 with some patience...
<br />

<br />
On the other hand I pretty much agree with Itchyban wrt end-game and other classes to look at. 
<br />
I'll add cleric/warrior/enchanter if you're really focused on end-game content. Enchanters can solo very well also. 
<br />

<br />
And don't forget bards!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
