			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Don't do it! 
<br />

<br />
In all seriousness, I suggest a hybrid preferably a ranger or SK (they get the most "get out of jail free cards)
<br />

<br />
Hybrids are nice for new people, you get the addition of many Hp's so you can live longer. You get the ease of /attack on as your main responsibility. Also you get to learn a little about spells and how they work. I remember when I started it took me like an hour to figure out how to mem a spell.  
<br />

<br />
However if you really wanna go w/ a pet caster... go Necro! Youll love it.  Caster's are much less dependent on gear than melee's. Thats nice when your lvl 20, however it gets to be a drag later in life when nothing you do makes you stronger... just makes you last longer on AE's 
<br />

<br />
Necro and SK quests:
<br />
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=35" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=35</a>
<br />

<br />
Ranger quests: (make your ranger Tunare <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=56" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/qsearch.html?zone=56</a>
<br />

<br />
PS. At level 4 you get your first pet. Make sure you save a few silvers to buy at least 1 malachite. You need it to cast your pet. That took me about 2 hours to figure out hah.<br />_________________<br />Ethari - Saryrn</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
