				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mage is a great class, there are shortcomings, but every class has them.  The mage class is very versatile and mages get pets that can take a beating (level 12 is when the pet tanks for you, up to that you tank for the pet  very often).  The mages that complain are mostly high end players who have only a handful of places where they can level and there the mages have a bit of a hard time.  There are pet bnalances coming, but if you are just starting, you won't feel any of this until you are in your 60s.
<br />

<br />
Mages can and do solo, and they can also group.  The main purpose of a mage is to do damage on a constant basis.  Until 50s, no other class in the game can put out dps like a mage and pet (at high levels you get mana regen items and such to bring wizards, druids and necros up there, otherwise  under 50 the other classes are constrained by mana, necros being the closest to the mage due to the pet and lich-line/lifetap-dot).
<br />

<br />
Mage class also requires you to be a better player.  You have no real defense except the pet, so you learn how agro works, how to pull singles, where to fight to avoid adds, how to nuke without overnuking, etc.  Playing a mage made me a better player overall.  It is a fun class to play.
<br />

<br />
At higher level the pets are quite powerful.  Milestone levels for a mage from my experience are: 24 (dual wield with 2 daggers), 39 (auto dual wield and much stronger pets, also known as the era of the fire pet, from 39-49 you mostly use fire pet for the huge damage shield), 61 (the era of the xegony air pet, allows you to solo to 65).  Level 51-61 are a bit tough for a mage, as the pets are not powerful enough to solo the blues you were used to up to that point, so the going gets a little tough until 61, you can still solo but not as quickly (the era of persistence).
<br />

<br />
Overall, check the hunting guides on this board and enjoy yourself.  Play a mage to 24 so you get the feel for the class and see if it is what you want to do.  (And don't forget to do the Sol Ro temple focus quests, search this board the guide is in the Library forum).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
