			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I think mages are a TON of fun to play.  My mage is only lvl 50, so I haven't seen the end game issues present with this class.  However, I usually play my warrior when it comes to raids.
<br />

<br />
That said...  I recommend a more global approach:  Try several classes.  You made a ranger? great!  Make a mage, make a bard, make a chanter, make a pally, or whatever.  Try them out for a few hours.  There's no reason to get attached to the very first class you choose.
<br />

<br />
Here's a tip regarding naming your toons...  I have 4 characters that I like to play on a regular basis:
<br />

<br />
Saeborne, Warrior
<br />
Saewhut, Mage
<br />
Saerien, Necro
<br />
Saerutt, Cleric
<br />

<br />
By keeping the different characters with similar names, it's easier for my friends to recognize me when I play an alt.  Roleplayers may not agree, but this system works well for me...
<br />

<br />
Oh, one last thing!  Use your /friend list...  It's a very good tool to keep track of people who's company you enjoy.  EQ is a very social game, and for me, the friendships that I've developed in game make it much more entertaining.
<br />

<br />
Welcome to EQ and I hope you find it as enjoyable as I have!!!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
