			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enigma was my very first Everquest Character a Half-Elf Ranger, on Veeshan, the day Veeshan went live.
<br />

<br />
I played Enigma intensively for about a month to a month and a half.  I and my friends were ks'd etc constantly (many of todays rules and code didn't exist them).  My friends played less, did less and easily leveled faster than Enigma (then there were racial and class penalties and I swear to God that half-Elf Rangers were at the very top of the penalty list).
<br />

<br />
Well a Magician and a Wizard combo easily ks'd us (2 rangers, 2 paladins and a warrior).  In a moment of pure frustration, I logged off and rolled a Wood Elf Druid.
<br />

<br />
What this story has to do with your question is this,  The Druid turned out to be everything I was looking for from my Ranger and a lot more powerful.  Enigma still exist were I left him at level 32.
<br />

<br />
If I were you, I would just forget the Production servers for a week or two.  Log onto Test Server and use the test server /testbuff command to make your character level 25, complete with 3 bags of equipment all spells and all Skills maxed.  Go play each race/class combination for a while and get a feel for what they can do.  At level 25 you can get a feel for what they can do.
<br />

<br />
While your doing the above, think about which of the two camps you are going to fall into
<br />

<br />
1) I play Everquest to have fun.  To enjoy the people I meet.
<br />
2) I play Everquest to beat it.  To be superior to all others.
<br />

<br />
By the time you have a good feel for the race/class's and have decided which camp you most fit in, then you will know the right race/class for you.
<br />

<br />
By the Way.  I did not see it mentioned, BUT if the Berserker class appeals to you, then you will need to purchase GoD.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
